#: Game.Levels.SetOpsWorld.L10_UnionCaseAnalysis
msgid "# Case Analysis: Splitting a Union Hypothesis\n"
"\n"
"So far you have been **proving** union membership (choosing §0 or\n"
"§1). Now you must **use** a union hypothesis — when you KNOW\n"
"§2 and must derive something from it.\n"
"\n"
"Since §3 is a disjunction, you handle it by **case analysis**:\n"
"consider the case §4 and the case §5 separately. The tactic\n"
"is §6:\n"
"\n"
"§7\n"
"\n"
"This creates two subgoals:\n"
"- **Case §8**: §9 in context (\"inject left\" — the left\n"
"  disjunct holds)\n"
"- **Case §10**: §11 in context (\"inject right\" — the right\n"
"  disjunct holds)\n"
"\n"
"Handle each subgoal with a §12 prefix, just like after §13.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove union commutativity at the element level. Given\n"
"§14, prove §15. You will need to \"swap sides\":\n"
"in the §16 case (knowing §17), use §18; in the §19 case\n"
"(knowing §20), use §21."
msgstr ""

