#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L12_SetNonEquality
msgid "You proved your first set **non-equality**! The proof structure was:\n"
"\n"
"1. **Assume** the sets are equal (§0)\n"
"2. **Exhibit** a witness element (3)\n"
"3. **Transport** membership using the equality (§1)\n"
"4. **Derive contradiction** from the impossible conclusion (§2)\n"
"\n"
"Compare this with Level 7 (disproving §3):\n"
"\n"
"| Goal | Assume | Witness | Contradiction from |\n"
"|---|---|---|---|\n"
"| §4 | §5 | element in §6 but not §7 | applying §8 to witness |\n"
"| §9 | §10 | element in one but not other | rewriting with §11 |\n"
"\n"
"Both use the same strategy — assume and contradict — but the mechanism\n"
"differs. For §12, you apply the subset hypothesis as a function. For\n"
"§13, you rewrite with the equality hypothesis to transport membership.\n"
"\n"
"In ordinary math: \"Suppose §14. Then\n"
"§15 (since §16 and the sets are equal).\n"
"But §17 is false. Contradiction.\""
msgstr ""

