#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L02_SetBuilder
msgid "# Set Builder Notation\n"
"\n"
"In mathematics, you write sets like §0.\n"
"In Lean, this becomes §1.\n"
"\n"
"This notation is syntactic sugar for §2, which is\n"
"defined as... just §3 itself! The function §4 is\n"
"literally the identity: it takes a predicate and returns it as a §5.\n"
"\n"
"So what happens when you check membership?\n"
"\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"The set builder notation just wraps a predicate. Membership evaluates\n"
"the predicate at the given point.\n"
"\n"
"**Look at your goal**: it says §7. We know this is\n"
"*definitionally* equal to §8, but some tactics (like §9)\n"
"need the goal in explicit arithmetic form to work.\n"
"\n"
"The §10 tactic converts the goal to a definitionally equal form.\n"
"Try §11 — this tells Lean to display the goal as §12\n"
"(which it can verify is the same thing). Then §13 closes it.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Use §14 then §15."
msgstr ""

