#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L04_InfiniteSet
msgid "# Sets Need Not Be Finite\n"
"\n"
"So far you have seen sets defined by arithmetic bounds like §0.\n"
"But predicates can describe infinite collections too.\n"
"\n"
"The set §1 contains all even natural numbers:\n"
"§2 — infinitely many elements.\n"
"\n"
"What does §3 mean? It is defined as:\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"So §5 unfolds to §6, which is §7.\n"
"\n"
"To prove an existential §8, you provide a **witness** — a\n"
"specific value of §9 — using the §10 tactic. Here, §11 turns\n"
"the goal into §12, which is true by computation.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that 4 is even by providing the witness §13.\n"
"Use §14."
msgstr ""

