#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L14_ProperSubset
msgid "# Strict Containment: The Proper Subset ⊂\n"
"\n"
"You have proved all three partial order axioms for §0 (reflexivity,\n"
"transitivity, antisymmetry). Antisymmetry says: if §1 and\n"
"§2, then §3. In other words, mutual containment forces\n"
"equality.\n"
"\n"
"But what about **strict** containment — when one set is inside\n"
"another but they are NOT equal? This is the **proper subset**\n"
"relation, written §4.\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, §5 means §6 — §7 is contained in\n"
"§8, and the containment is strict (there is something in §9 that is\n"
"not in §10).\n"
"\n"
"To prove §11, use §12 to split into two goals:\n"
"1. Prove §13 — a familiar subset proof\n"
"2. Prove §14 — a familiar non-subset proof (Level 7)\n"
"\n"
"This level integrates two skills you have already mastered!\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §15 — split §16 into §17 and §18\n"
"2. **First goal** (§19): prove the subset as in Level 1\n"
"3. **Second goal** (§20): disprove the reverse as in Level 7"
msgstr ""

