#: Game.Levels.SetOpsWorld.L01_UnionMembership
msgid "# Set Operations: Union\n"
"\n"
"In the last two worlds, you learned that sets are predicates and that\n"
"subset/equality proofs reduce to propositional logic. Now you will learn\n"
"the **set operations** — union, intersection, complement, and difference —\n"
"and see that each one corresponds to a logical connective.\n"
"\n"
"The first operation is **union**. The union of two sets §0 and §1,\n"
"written §2, contains every element that belongs to §3 **or** §4\n"
"(or both):\n"
"\n"
"§5\n"
"\n"
"So union IS disjunction. When you need to prove §6, you are\n"
"proving a disjunction. You choose which side to prove using two new\n"
"tactics:\n"
"\n"
"- §7 — reduces the goal to the left disjunct (§8)\n"
"- §9 — reduces the goal to the right disjunct (§10)\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that 3 is in the union of two sets. Since §11,\n"
"the left set contains 3, so use §12.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. §13 — choose the left disjunct (3 is in the left set)\n"
"2. §14 — unfold the set-builder membership\n"
"3. §15 — close the arithmetic goal"
msgstr ""

