msgid "You just used a subset hypothesis as a function for the first time!\n"
"\n"
"The key insight: §0 is not just a statement — it is a\n"
"**function** that converts membership proofs. Given §1,\n"
"the expression §2 is a proof of §3.\n"
"\n"
"| Expression | Type | Meaning |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| §4 | §5 | \"every element of s is in t\" |\n"
"| §6 | §7 | \"x is in s\" |\n"
"| §8 | §9 | \"therefore x is in t\" |\n"
"\n"
"This pattern — applying a subset hypothesis to a membership proof —\n"
"is the fundamental way to *use* subset facts. You will chain multiple\n"
"such applications in the next levels."
msgstr ""

