#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L06_SubsetHypAsFunction
msgid "# Using a Subset Hypothesis\n"
"\n"
"So far, you have been **proving** subset relations from scratch using\n"
"§0. But what about **using** a subset hypothesis that you\n"
"already have?\n"
"\n"
"If §1, then §2 is essentially a **function**: give it a\n"
"proof that §3, and it returns a proof that §4. This is\n"
"because §5 unfolds to §6, which is exactly\n"
"the type of a function from membership proofs to membership proofs.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, you have §7 and §8. Your goal is\n"
"§9. Since §10 is a function that takes §11 to §12,\n"
"you can close the goal with §13.\n"
"\n"
"Alternatively, you can use §14 to reduce the goal from §15\n"
"to §16, then close with §17.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"- §18 — apply §19 to §20 directly\n"
"- OR: §21 then §22 — reduce goal, then close"
msgstr ""

